CATEGORIES:Podcast - TWiV
DESCRIPTION:[Podcast: This Week in Virology]\n\nTWiV explains the emergenc
 e of vaccine-derived poliovirus strains from the novel oral polio vaccine 
 in the Central African Republic\, and the infection of spiral ganglion neu
 rons in the inner ear by SARS-CoV-2\, which may explain hearing loss in hu
 mans. Hosts:&nbsp\; Vincent Racaniello \, Alan Dove \, and Kathy Spindler 
 Click arrow to play Download TWiV 1319 (62MB .mp3\, 104 min) Subscribe (fr
 ee):&nbsp\; Apple Podcasts \,&nbsp\; RSS \,&nbsp\; email Become a&nbsp\; p
 atron &nbsp\;of&nbsp\;TWiV! Links for this episode Support science educati
 on at MicrobeTV 4:58 Positions in Rosenfeld Lab (email) 5:13 Bernard Roizm
 an dies (U Chicago) 7:50 Craig Venter dies (Sci Am) 8:11 Trump fires Natio
 nal Science Board (AAU) 9:46 It was World Vaccine Week (WHO) 10:33 nOPV2 p
 henotypically reverts via recombination (mBio) 11:58 SARS-CoV-2 infects in
 ner ear (Cell Rep) 36:50 Letters read on TWiV 1319 1:06:58 Timestamps by&n
 bsp\; Jolene Ramsey. Thanks! Weekly Picks 1:28:02 Kathy &#8211\; Science o
 f rats and other organisms in the East River Alan &#8211\; Chronolog citiz
 en science project Vincent &#8211\; Why Do Train Engines Sometimes Face Ba
 ckwards? Listener Picks Chris &#8211\; Consensus: AI for research Intro mu
 sic is by&nbsp\; Ronald Jenkees Send your virology questions and comments 
 to twiv@microbe.tv Content in this podcast should not be construed as medi
 cal advice. The post TWiV 1319: An earful of SARS-CoV-2 first appeared on 
 This Week in Virology .\n\nEvent URL: https://www.microbe.tv/twiv/twiv-131
 9/\n\nSource: twiv_podcast
LOCATION:Podcast
URL:https://www.microbe.tv/twiv/twiv-1319/
