 ons in Rosenfeld Lab (email) 3:43 Craig Venter dies (Nature) 5:11 Hantavir
 us outbreak (WHO) 9:33 Hantavirus on board (YouTube) 10:00 HPS 25th annive
 rsary discovery story (EID) 10:12 Phage therapeutic failure unraveled (Nat
  Med) 17:23 Phages communicate across species (Cell) 48:37 Control of lysi
 s-lysogeny decisions (Trends Micro) Arbitrium phages manipulate each other
  (Cell) Elio Schaechter on arbitrium ( TWiM 146 ) Letters read on TWiV 132
 1 1:27:13 Timestamps by&nbsp\; Jolene Ramsey. Thanks! Weekly Picks 1:38:42
  Brianne &#8211\; Could this fungus contaminate Mars? Rich &#8211\; Supern
 ova in a Sideways Spiral Jolene &#8211\; Virology class communication proj
 ects 2026 Vincent &#8211\; Facts About The Boeing 747 Hump That Will Surpr
 ise You Listener Picks David &#8211\; My first science video in 3 years In
 tro music is by&nbsp\; Ronald Jenkees Send your virology questions and com
 ments to twiv@microbe.tv Content in this podcast should not be construed a
 s medical advic\n\nEvent URL: https://www.microbe.tv/twiv/twiv-1321/\n\nSo
 urce: twiv_podcast
